<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Boanerges on 05-03-2001 05:02 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">  [QUOTE]1) Make Plasmatic Priest much harder. For example, level 60 and totally MR would be a start.[/QUOTE]
Not a bad idea but very hard to pull off. He's pretty resistant now AND unstunable. Adding all those spells from 55 to 60 increases the risk that one of those NPCs will poof him, thus forcing a restart. I sure as heck don't want to add to the frustration already present in this #^$* quest.
 [QUOTE]2) Make Overking harder.
[/QUOTE]
Again, he's already pretty tough. AE dispell, ability to CH and some nasty AE damage makes him hard for the average guild. A better solution is to make the drop rate less. Honestly, I was anxious to complete this step before Verant nerfed it and I'm surprised they haven't. No other quest has an unPHed mob like this with a 100% drop rate (at least before they made the Queen have 100% drops which they needed to since she is 10x harder than the king.). 30-50% drop rate would be fine really. Especially since many clerics sailed through this step thanks to uberguild X who let them loot it rather than letting it rot.
 [QUOTE]3) Make Ixiblat harder.[/QUOTE]
He's level 60. He can double hit for 575. he has Nagafen's AE fire. And he needs buffing because...? Don't touch the mob. Just make the quest giver despawn like the rest of the quest. No more "Ixblat nights". Problem solved.
 [QUOTE]4) Make epic effect only work at 56+. Since I've heard that effects can only be set at 50, then make it so the quest givers only talk to 55+ Clerics. Sorry for all you lower level Clerics, but my feeling is you should be able to cast the spell before you can use the effect. Go level up a bit.[/QUOTE]
Honestly, if they make the quest harder you're more than welcome to the 56 res before 56. Keep in mind that we look like hypocrites if we make a stink about people demanding 56 reses over 49 and then say that the 56 res is too good for a 50-55 cleric to have. It's either a huge difference or it's not all that different. Take your pick.
 [QUOTE]5) Leave Ragefire where he is, but add a triggerable mob (ala Feydedar) that is low 60s and requires 4-5 good groups to kill. This allows the weaker guilds a chance to get an easy Ragefire while the stronger guilds can go after the triggered mob. Put the trigger mob on a 12/24 hour timer.[/QUOTE]

Uhm... what about Nagafen? That's still my biggest problem, really. Naggy is still level capped. While it makes sense story-wise I don't think we should have to deal with Naggy. Move him to Skyshrine and tie him into Talendor (uncapped level 60 Naggy) and do the rest of what you said.


------------------
Boanerges Thundercry
Erudite Templar of Prexus
Cohort Chalybeius
Cazic Thule Server

